header.gameNote: SOUTHLAND CONF TR AT HOUSTON TX

article.headline: Northwestern St. 85, Stephen F. Austin 76
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Reserve Keithan Hancock's 3-pointer with 4:39 to play ignited a 12-3 run that allowed third-seeded Northwestern State to hold off sixth seed Stephen F. Austin 85-76 in a Southland Conference first-round tournament game Thursday. Hancock's shot broke a 73-73 tie with 4:39 to play. It was his only 3-pointer of the game in five attempts. Luke Rogers led the Demons with 18 points, including 13 in the first half, when Northwestern State built a 39-31 lead. Northwestern State (16-14) will play Lamar in the tournament semifinals Friday. Trey Gilder scored 14 and Kennan Jones added 13 for the Demons. Jermaine Spencer scored 12 points and added nine rebounds. SFA (15-14) opened the second half with a 17-8 run to take a 48-47 lead with 16:08 left. The Lumberjacks built the lead to six before going cold and turning the ball over down the stretch. SFA, which was led by Chaz Dykes' career-high 17 points, committed 19 turnovers. Matt Kingsley had 16 points for the Lumberjacks, who suffered their eighth loss in 10 games.
